etting muddled with the cbor extension’s registration process. That clarity will help me make the most of my testing efforts.\\n\\n**Evaluating test requirements**\\n\\nI might need to test the library meaningfully, but the instructions say to only modify the test file. It seems I should avoid updating the build.gradle unless essential for dependencies or classpath. I'm wondering about the `@Serializable` object; I can't compile it without the plugin. The task emphasizes comprehensive tests, which might justify adding a plugin. Maybe I can use manual built-in serializers directly with `Cbor.encodeToByteArray`, but I feel like it complicates things too much. I’ll think about avoiding direct serialization methods.\\n\\n**Testing CBOR serialization**\\n\\nI need to test the `cbor()` registration for both default and custom content types, and round-trip serialization for lists and maps. I wonder if the converter can handle nullable values, like returning null if the value is null—maybe I should avoid that. I also need to check if the default CBOR is set up to use `encodeDefaults` through the public API. Does CBOR have a `serializersModule`? I’m considering if the configuration is handled through properties.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_032a0cd35e800ca80169fa6b06215c8195b342a5bb929c7557\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-msW-R2qLf4rv01Rb4Ui08fAjnlMKUDQQMqdmhrhrNtbx5Q_idKBxYSCDPp3fQMl2fFebL31RNEF2tKVdtEtOOQO08BoHA1l4bopddVtZ5ZIa1Kbiepl81S20FyQtBFpgqyG6ASTrWhv4Ra-6IDlYlwMzgq6DppZbEpBGDOXraNQ2JtQJEyc5EXhuOs7FpRiF-L2VU5VnILsq6Nd5cVlJ-J4Rh7D48V89zjbTrRW6K9hewhWVBoXDqAMn1WL21ztRYrHgkApL_4w3dgimRHA90PPvBmdONpd3LuSpsh5s5zjsGIqLZs-O3XhgXX0QXWaLidNRSDzSCVNjsqzcuiEoYIqFZi9B0jNmDc3l9InwAo0FA2KU2IRYgibjHX2L87Uv3kUiA8WwcuQ7KL7klE6RTv-m4WWEEB7HOUY22rfV_SzjTUW199FdV-G6k4ydTCgFDZmnNRXbsF1Bkq_BvNuO0JJ3yFvm-qL9E6k_93hB4fr2TX5dEFcfA_P-uAhtx45mHFJQnbxm-wRbgdcPsmWM0cglYuKhmIC5tMf_oEiNC4Ap2C0l48Aex-2QSn9SbByYMknqcGDYhd4Ig8DZ0T3DWptjyEsb1