rocess. That clarity will help me make the most of my testing efforts.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test requirements**\\\\n\\\\nI might need to test the library meaningfully, but the instructions say to only modify the test file. It seems I should avoid updating the build.gradle unless essential for dependencies or classpath. I'm wondering about the `@Serializable` object; I can't compile it without the plugin. The task emphasizes comprehensive tests, which might justify adding a plugin. Maybe I can use manual built-in serializers directly with `Cbor.encodeToByteArray`, but I feel like it complicates things too much. I’ll think about avoiding direct serialization methods.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Testing CBOR serialization**\\\\n\\\\nI need to test the `cbor()` registration for both default and custom content types, and round-trip serialization for lists and maps. I wonder if the converter can handle nullable values, like returning null if the value is null—maybe I should avoid that. I also need to check if the default CBOR is set up to use `encodeDefaults` through the public API. Does CBOR have a `serializersModule`? I’m considering if the configuration is handled through properties.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_5FOzYamnKfHyDqV7iS15YA5W|fc_032a0cd35e800ca80169fa6b16fa648195875b2560d03e401e\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm -type f -name '*.jar' | tail -1\"}, \"partialJson\": \"{\\\"command\\\":\\\"find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm -type f -name '*.jar' | tail -1\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1342, \"output\": 1087, \"cacheRead\": 24064, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 26493, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0